parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Heater core failure can cause hot coolant to leak into the passenger compartment, leading to fogged windows, impaired visibility, and potential breathing difficulties. In some cases, it can also cause the vehicle to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: Hot coolant leaks into the passenger compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Short in Door and Window System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical short in the door and window system can cause the driver's door to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to open or close, and the window to stick, which can lead to safety issues and inconvenience.
symptoms: Driver's door will not unlatch from the outside

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty heater core can cause coolant to leak, leading to a strong, suffocating smell inside the vehicle, and potentially causing overheating issues.
symptoms: Strong coolant smell inside the vehicle
loud noise when the heater is turned on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine cooling system failures can cause overheating, which can lead to engine damage, stalling, or even fires.
symptoms: strong coolant smell inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Gasket failures can cause coolant or oil leaks, leading to overheating issues, engine damage, or other problems.
symptoms: strong coolant or oil smell inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause issues with the engine, brakes, or other systems, leading to stalling, overheating, or other problems.
Brake system failures can cause loss of braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
Catalytic converter failures can cause issues with the engine, leading to stalling, overheating, or other problems.
Electrical system failures can cause the vehicle to shut off while driving, catch fire, or experience other safety-critical issues, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: inability to shut off the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failure can cause the battery to drain, leading to electrical system failures, stalling, and potentially even fires.
Ignition system failures can cause the vehicle to stall or have difficulty starting, which can lead to accidents or strand the driver.
Cooling system failures can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage or even fires.
The failure of the brake rotors can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Brake rotors separate from the wheel hub

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake system can cause the brakes to stick and wear out other brake parts, leading to premature wear and potential brake failure.
